  <title translate="true">RMA: Defining Hydraulic Conductivity</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">RMA: Defining Hydraulic Conductivity</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="RMA_Study_Area_Description" anchor="TableOfProperties" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Study Area Description</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the hydraulic conductivity is specified as 0.0001 m/s. To set that select </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Data|Edit Data Sets...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> &#160;Then in the tree control on the left, expand </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Required|Hydrology</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and select </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Kx</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;For the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Default formula</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, enter 0.0001. &#160;Then click the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Apply</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button.</text></para>
  </body>
